WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.084 --> 00:00:02.001
[Debbie] My name is Debbie Claybourne.

2
00:00:02.086 --> 00:00:03.921
I thought my marriage was strong.

3
00:00:04.003 --> 00:00:05.506
Think we should get a divorce.

4
00:00:05.589 --> 00:00:07.383
[upbeat. dramatic music playing]

5
00:00:07.466 --> 00:00:09.343
-[gasps]
-Judith!

6
00:00:09.427 --> 00:00:11.178
I thought I knew my best friend.

7
00:00:11.262 --> 00:00:13.347
[grunting]

8
00:00:13.431 --> 00:00:15.891
-Are you an assassin?
-Yep.

9
00:00:15.975 --> 00:00:17.143
[Judith] My name is Whiptail.

10
00:00:17.226 --> 00:00:19.311
I am an international assassin.

11
00:00:19.395 --> 00:00:20.312
[screaming]

12
00:00:20.396 --> 00:00:21.897
Is that my next assignment?

13
00:00:21.981 --> 00:00:23.315
Billy Donovan?

14
00:00:23.399 --> 00:00:25.168
[Sam] You were the gold standard.
and now everything you touch

15
00:00:25.192 --> 00:00:26.277
turns into chaos.

16
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:27.862
-[gunshots]
-[screaming]

17
00:00:27.945 --> 00:00:29.381
[Debbie] Why are they shooting at us?

18
00:00:29.405 --> 00:00:30.823
Why do you have a gun?

19
00:00:32.366 --> 00:00:35.953
[Judith] And now. both our lives have
been completely turned upside down.

20
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:37.204
It's the Black Mark.

21
00:00:37.288 --> 00:00:39.048
Pirate code.
It means someone wants you dead.

22
00:00:39.081 --> 00:00:40.291
♪♪

23
00:00:40.374 --> 00:00:42.585
I know how to find them.

24
00:00:42.668 --> 00:00:43.919
I've been shot at.

25
00:00:44.003 --> 00:00:45.003
I've been chased.

26
00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:47.798
I drove a vehicle I'm not even insured on.

27
00:00:47.882 --> 00:00:48.924
And my husband...

28
00:00:49.008 --> 00:00:50.468
There's something

29
00:00:50.551 --> 00:00:52.191
that I think you should know about David.

30
00:00:53.637 --> 00:00:55.639
-He's dead.
-He left me.

31
00:00:55.723 --> 00:00:57.099
-What?
-What?

32
00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:00.870
-[♪ Meredith Brooks singing "Bitch"]
-♪ I hate the world today ♪

33
00:01:01.479 --> 00:01:05.733
♪ You're so good to me.
I know. but I can't change ♪

34
00:01:06.692 --> 00:01:08.319
♪ Tried to tell you ♪

35
00:01:08.402 --> 00:01:10.321
♪ I don't envy you ♪

36
00:01:10.404 --> 00:01:15.367
♪ I'm a little bit of everything
all rolled into one ♪

37
00:01:15.451 --> 00:01:17.870
♪ I'm a bitch. I'm a lover ♪

38
00:01:17.953 --> 00:01:21.164
♪ I'm a child. I'm a mother.
I'm a sinner...

39
00:01:21.248 --> 00:01:23.542
[dispatcher] All units.
armed response team.

40
00:01:23.626 --> 00:01:27.463
Northwood Hills.
Report of gunfire on B34.

41
00:01:27.545 --> 00:01:28.923
Witnesses suggest single driver.

42
00:01:29.006 --> 00:01:30.132
Possibly female.

43
00:01:30.216 --> 00:01:31.509
Shit.

44
00:01:32.718 --> 00:01:34.720
[mysterious music playing]

45
00:01:43.229 --> 00:01:44.896
Jackpot.

46
00:01:47.942 --> 00:01:48.943
You okay?

47
00:01:50.402 --> 00:01:52.196
I don't know what's wrong with it.

48
00:01:54.657 --> 00:01:57.660
[Debbie] Oh. my God. your car is so tidy.

49
00:01:57.743 --> 00:02:00.704
Mine is filled to the brim.
I just throw everything in the front seat.

50
00:02:00.788 --> 00:02:02.414
-[sighs]
-Plus. I have to have my seat

51
00:02:02.498 --> 00:02:04.041
all the way back because I'm pregnant.

52
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:07.670
Arms completely straight.
[chuckles] Oh. God.

53
00:02:07.753 --> 00:02:08.795
Is that a seat warmer?

54
00:02:08.878 --> 00:02:11.465
I love a good seat Warner. Just...

55
00:02:12.675 --> 00:02:14.635
What? Why are you smiling?

56
00:02:14.718 --> 00:02:17.012
You... talk quite a lot.

57
00:02:17.096 --> 00:02:19.139
I do. I'm sorry.

58
00:02:19.223 --> 00:02:20.534
-I'm sorry. [laughs]
-Oh. no. no. no. no.

59
00:02:20.558 --> 00:02:23.227
No. no. no. it's... actually really nice.

60
00:02:23.310 --> 00:02:26.647
I have a bit of a serious. boring job.

61
00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:29.149
I don't really get to chat much.

62
00:02:29.233 --> 00:02:30.985
Oh. what do you do?

63
00:02:32.361 --> 00:02:33.779
I'm a forensic accountant.

64
00:02:33.863 --> 00:02:35.406
[sighs]

65
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:37.074
Fascinating.

66
00:02:37.156 --> 00:02:38.868
Tell me everything.

67
00:02:38.951 --> 00:02:41.579
[lighthearted music playing]

68
00:02:41.662 --> 00:02:43.932
[Judith] Yeah. but did you read
the second book? Because I thought...

69
00:02:43.956 --> 00:02:45.708
-Not as good.
-Not as good.

70
00:02:45.791 --> 00:02:46.834
He rested on his laurels.

71
00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:48.293
A hundred percent.

72
00:02:48.377 --> 00:02:49.729
-It felt rushed.
-That's exactly right.

73
00:02:49.753 --> 00:02:51.505
It felt rushed.

74
00:02:51.589 --> 00:02:52.965
[Debbie laughs]

75
00:02:53.048 --> 00:02:55.466
[both singing along] ♪ I'm a bitch.
I'm a lover ♪

76
00:02:55.551 --> 00:02:57.720
♪ I'm a child. I'm a mother ♪

77
00:02:57.803 --> 00:03:00.723
♪ I'm a sinner. I'm a saint ♪

78
00:03:00.806 --> 00:03:03.726
♪ I do not feel ashamed. I'm your...

79
00:03:03.809 --> 00:03:05.060
Oh! Sorry. sorry.

80
00:03:05.144 --> 00:03:06.186
-Oh. no.
-That's me.

81
00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:08.230
Oh. Oh.

82
00:03:08.314 --> 00:03:11.317
♪ You know you wouldn't
want it any other...

83
00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:12.720
-[song shuts off]
-[engine idling]

84
00:03:12.776 --> 00:03:13.944
[sighs]

85
00:03:14.028 --> 00:03:15.905
[chuckles] Well...

86
00:03:15.988 --> 00:03:17.031
it was lovely to meet you.

87
00:03:17.114 --> 00:03:18.282
You. too.

88
00:03:19.283 --> 00:03:20.910
[chuckles]

89
00:03:29.627 --> 00:03:30.628
[rolls down window]

90
00:03:30.711 --> 00:03:31.754
-Hi.
-Hi.

91
00:03:31.837 --> 00:03:33.797
-Hey.
-Hey.

92
00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:35.630
Would you like to come in?

93
00:03:37.593 --> 00:03:39.345
-Yeah.
-[chuckles]

94
00:03:39.428 --> 00:03:40.804
Yeah. I'd like that.

95
00:03:40.888 --> 00:03:42.890
[quiet. pulsing music playing]

96
00:03:44.391 --> 00:03:46.393
[garage door opening]

97
00:03:53.067 --> 00:03:55.027
Where is this? Where are we going?

98
00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:57.363
Uh. my house.

99
00:03:57.446 --> 00:03:59.007
-[pulls hand brake]
-What are you talking about?

100
00:03:59.031 --> 00:04:00.508
This isn't your house.
I've been to your house.

101
00:04:00.532 --> 00:04:01.742
That's not my real house.

102
00:04:02.910 --> 00:04:04.161
You have a fake house?

103
00:04:04.244 --> 00:04:05.746
No. it's a real house.

104
00:04:05.829 --> 00:04:07.414
-I just don't...
-Who has a fake house?

105
00:04:07.498 --> 00:04:10.960
You know what? You know what?
[laughs] I cannot deal with this!

106
00:04:11.043 --> 00:04:12.878
I don't want to hear about
your fake house.

107
00:04:12.962 --> 00:04:15.547
or your fake life. or your fake friends.

108
00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:20.427
My husband is dead.

109
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:22.346
And I need

110
00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:24.723
to call my children
and tell them their dad

111
00:04:24.807 --> 00:04:26.642
is some kind of criminal.

112
00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:28.727
So I want to go to my normal.

113
00:04:28.811 --> 00:04:30.187
real house.

114
00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:33.107
Well. you can't. It's too dangerous.

115
00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:34.108
Take me home. Judith.

116
00:04:34.191 --> 00:04:36.235
No. Get in the house.

117
00:04:36.318 --> 00:04:37.861
-No!
-Fine!

118
00:04:37.945 --> 00:04:39.405
Then stay in the van.

119
00:04:39.488 --> 00:04:40.531
[Debbie] Fine.

120
00:04:40.614 --> 00:04:41.824
I will!

121
00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:44.784
[scoffs]

122
00:04:46.328 --> 00:04:47.705
All right. I'm coming.

123
00:04:47.788 --> 00:04:49.790
[♪ Gin Wigmore sings "Kill of the Night"]

124
00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:57.715
♪ The street's a liar ♪

125
00:04:58.799 --> 00:05:02.219
♪ I'm gonna lure you into the dark ♪

126
00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:05.723
♪ My cold desire ♪

127
00:05:05.806 --> 00:05:09.727
♪ to hear the boom. boom. boom
of your heart ♪

128
00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:14.273
♪ The danger is I'm dangerous ♪

129
00:05:14.356 --> 00:05:17.234
♪ And I might just tear you apart ♪

130
00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:21.155
♪ Oh. ah. oh ♪

131
00:05:22.239 --> 00:05:24.074
♪ I'm gonna catch ya ♪

132
00:05:24.158 --> 00:05:26.035
♪ I'm gonna get ya. get ya ♪

133
00:05:26.118 --> 00:05:28.120
♪ Oh. ah. oh ♪

134
00:05:28.954 --> 00:05:34.710
♪ I wanna taste the way
that you bleed. oh ♪

135
00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:42.801
♪ You're my kill of the ♪

136
00:05:42.885 --> 00:05:45.888
♪ night ♪♪

137
00:05:50.601 --> 00:05:52.561
Me again. Whiptail. Just checking in.

138
00:05:52.644 --> 00:05:55.105
Keen to hear where we're
at vis-à-vis us being in shit

139
00:05:55.189 --> 00:05:57.441
up to and including our eyeballs.
Where are you?

140
00:05:57.524 --> 00:05:58.524
[woman clears throat]

141
00:05:58.567 --> 00:05:59.777
Amanda.

142
00:05:59.860 --> 00:06:01.111
Uh. I was just looking for you.

143
00:06:01.195 --> 00:06:02.362
-Where is she?
-She is

144
00:06:02.446 --> 00:06:05.741
collecting. uh. data
and regrouping for a second pass.

145
00:06:05.824 --> 00:06:07.117
You don't know where she is.

146
00:06:07.201 --> 00:06:08.744
You've lost control of your agent.

147
00:06:08.827 --> 00:06:10.547
and she's failed
to complete her assignment.

148
00:06:10.579 --> 00:06:11.914
I absolutely do know.

149
00:06:11.997 --> 00:06:13.916
The Director made himself very clear.

150
00:06:13.999 --> 00:06:15.918
Last night was her final chance.

151
00:06:16.001 --> 00:06:17.252
I will let The Director know.

152
00:06:17.336 --> 00:06:18.253
No. please.

153
00:06:18.337 --> 00:06:19.939
Just-just hang on.
She's got this. I promise.

154
00:06:19.963 --> 00:06:21.256
-[phone buzzing]
-Ah! You see?

155
00:06:21.340 --> 00:06:23.675
Just hold those horses.

156
00:06:23.759 --> 00:06:24.760
Yes?

157
00:06:24.843 --> 00:06:27.763
[Barry] Sorry. boss.
looked everywhere. She's vanished.

158
00:06:27.846 --> 00:06:31.391
Okay. okay. just. um...
[chuckles] Just come back in.

159
00:06:31.475 --> 00:06:33.477
[quiet. tense music playing]

160
00:06:42.945 --> 00:06:45.614
So. your work bought this for you?

161
00:06:45.697 --> 00:06:47.116
No.

162
00:06:47.199 --> 00:06:49.451
The Agency don't know anything
about this place.

163
00:06:51.745 --> 00:06:52.788
Nobody does.

164
00:06:54.373 --> 00:06:56.500
You designed all this on your own?

165
00:06:57.417 --> 00:06:58.544
Mm-hmm.

166
00:06:59.628 --> 00:07:01.547
Absolutely lovely.

167
00:07:01.630 --> 00:07:03.340
[mysterious. dramatic music playing]

168
00:07:05.092 --> 00:07:06.135
[sighs]

169
00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:13.308
Where's all your stuff?

170
00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:16.103
Where's your antiques?

171
00:07:30.701 --> 00:07:32.953
Do you know
you have guns in the cooker?

172
00:07:34.538 --> 00:07:35.664
Yes.

173
00:07:35.747 --> 00:07:37.791
Who are you?

174
00:07:37.875 --> 00:07:41.795
I'm the same person I've always been.
Deb. I'm your friend.

175
00:07:41.879 --> 00:07:43.755
I'm exactly who you think I am.

176
00:07:43.839 --> 00:07:45.382
-I just...
-Look at where we are.

177
00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.259
What kind of person lives like this?

178
00:07:47.342 --> 00:07:51.263
The person I was friends with isn't real.

179
00:07:51.346 --> 00:07:53.682
You lied to me. David lied to me.

180
00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:55.475
He divorced me. now he's dead.

181
00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:59.563
and the one person I want to call
and tell has guns in the cooker.

182
00:08:01.815 --> 00:08:03.817
[stammers]

183
00:08:12.159 --> 00:08:13.327
Wait. where are you going?

184
00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:14.411
I need

185
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:16.830
to go into work and find out
who left me this. okay?

186
00:08:16.914 --> 00:08:20.042
Now. will you please just take a shower?
There's plenty of food in.

187
00:08:20.125 --> 00:08:23.045
and I will get back to you
as soon as I can.

188
00:08:23.128 --> 00:08:24.588
I am not staying here.

189
00:08:24.671 --> 00:08:26.048
Well. you can't come with me

190
00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:27.674
and I can't leave you anywhere else.

191
00:08:27.758 --> 00:08:29.468
I have to keep you safe.

192
00:08:31.595 --> 00:08:35.015
But I promise you. when all this is over.

193
00:08:35.097 --> 00:08:37.058
I will explain everything.

194
00:08:38.936 --> 00:08:40.770
Now. please just trust me.

195
00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:43.315
[scoffs] Trust you?

196
00:08:43.398 --> 00:08:46.401
Honey. when this is over.
I don't ever want to see you again.

197
00:08:55.869 --> 00:08:57.079
Keep it together.

198
00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:00.666
You got to call the kids.
And tell them what?

199
00:09:00.749 --> 00:09:02.709
"Hi. kids. it's Mom.

200
00:09:02.793 --> 00:09:04.503
It's Mom and your dad is..."

201
00:09:06.046 --> 00:09:08.298
Don't panic. Debbie.
Don't panic. Don't panic!

202
00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:10.801
You have to tell them.

203
00:09:12.135 --> 00:09:13.595
You have to tell them.

204
00:09:14.721 --> 00:09:16.932
Or else they're going
to find out from the news.

205
00:09:17.015 --> 00:09:18.350
The news.

206
00:09:18.433 --> 00:09:20.936
Oh. my God. the news.

207
00:09:21.019 --> 00:09:23.605
[tense. rhythmic music playing]

208
00:09:23.689 --> 00:09:27.150
David Clybourne garden party?

209
00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:29.903
David... Claybourne... dead.

210
00:09:30.988 --> 00:09:33.115
"David Claybourne dead certain

211
00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:34.908
cost of living will go down."

212
00:09:34.992 --> 00:09:36.326
What?

213
00:09:37.828 --> 00:09:39.955
[telephone ringing]

214
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:41.331
Hello. the Hotel Mont Claire.

215
00:09:41.415 --> 00:09:43.250
Yes. my name is Debbie Claybourne.

216
00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:44.334
Hello. Mrs. Claybourne.

217
00:09:45.419 --> 00:09:49.214
Uh. I-I'm trying to locate my husband.
David Claybourne.

218
00:09:49.298 --> 00:09:51.550
Absolutely. Is he a guest with us?

219
00:09:51.633 --> 00:09:55.012
No. he... was...

220
00:09:56.221 --> 00:09:58.265
involved with the incident last night.

221
00:09:58.348 --> 00:10:00.058
Which incident was that?

222
00:10:01.935 --> 00:10:03.145
At the party?

223
00:10:03.228 --> 00:10:05.856
The-the terrible thing?

224
00:10:07.649 --> 00:10:08.900
The people... in-in-in

225
00:10:08.984 --> 00:10:10.736
in Billy Donovan's hotel room?

226
00:10:10.819 --> 00:10:13.238
Ah. yes. madame. the terrible thing.

227
00:10:13.322 --> 00:10:16.992
We were notified that
Mr. Donovan's room had a mold infestation.

228
00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:19.870
and a rapid remediation team
were brought in to clean the area.

229
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:22.015
Uh. I can assure you.
the incident has been entirely resolved

230
00:10:22.039 --> 00:10:23.457
and the rest of the hotel

231
00:10:23.540 --> 00:10:24.875
-is absolutely safe.
-But...

232
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:26.644
Was your husband
involved in that situation?

233
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:28.420
Did he...
did he touch the mold in any way?

234
00:10:28.503 --> 00:10:29.546
[call beeps off]

235
00:10:31.548 --> 00:10:32.549
[cell phone buzzing]

236
00:10:32.632 --> 00:10:34.634
[groans] Hello.

237
00:10:34.718 --> 00:10:35.635
[Debbie] Where is my husband's body?

238
00:10:35.719 --> 00:10:38.180
The Agency have got it... him.

239
00:10:38.263 --> 00:10:39.931
uh. and he's com-completely safe...

240
00:10:40.015 --> 00:10:42.309
No. no. no. no. no.
A mold company has him.

241
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:44.728
How do you know that?

242
00:10:44.811 --> 00:10:46.104
I called the hotel.

243
00:10:46.188 --> 00:10:47.773
-Why would you do that?
-Why wouldn't I?

244
00:10:47.856 --> 00:10:49.274
He wasn't on the news.

245
00:10:49.358 --> 00:10:50.859
Well. of course he's not on the news.

246
00:10:50.942 --> 00:10:52.778
I told you. the Agency

247
00:10:52.861 --> 00:10:54.154
have taken care of everything.

248
00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:55.655
Who are these people?

249
00:10:55.739 --> 00:10:57.741
[sighs]

250
00:10:57.824 --> 00:10:59.284
You don't want to know.

251
00:10:59.368 --> 00:11:01.370
[tense. dramatic music playing]

252
00:11:06.583 --> 00:11:08.502
[cell phone buzzing]

253
00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:13.298
-Thank God. Is it done?
-Is what done?

254
00:11:13.382 --> 00:11:14.841
Billy Donovan. Is he dead?

255
00:11:14.925 --> 00:11:16.718
Not yet.

256
00:11:16.802 --> 00:11:18.095
Listen.

257
00:11:18.178 --> 00:11:20.347
there was a body from last night.

258
00:11:20.430 --> 00:11:21.848
Look. last night's under control.

259
00:11:21.932 --> 00:11:24.184
-Footage is deleted. scene is clear.
-No. no. no.

260
00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:26.603
I need you to hold onto a body for me.

261
00:11:26.686 --> 00:11:28.355
Just... keep it safe.

262
00:11:28.438 --> 00:11:29.356
What? Whose body?

263
00:11:29.439 --> 00:11:32.442
[sighs] Uh. a guy called David Claybourne.

264
00:11:32.526 --> 00:11:33.819
He's an MP.

265
00:11:33.902 --> 00:11:35.529
An MP?

266
00:11:35.612 --> 00:11:37.072
You shot an MP?

267
00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:39.157
I didn't shoot him. He was already dead.

268
00:11:39.241 --> 00:11:40.242
No. no. of course.

269
00:11:40.325 --> 00:11:41.952
because nothing's ever your fault. Yes.

270
00:11:42.035 --> 00:11:43.262
I will go down and get your body back.

271
00:11:43.286 --> 00:11:45.539
Now. will you please.
please go and do your job?

272
00:11:45.622 --> 00:11:47.249
I'm coming in.

273
00:11:47.332 --> 00:11:49.084
[tires screech]

274
00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:51.002
-Hello?
-[telephone rings]

275
00:11:51.086 --> 00:11:52.170
What?

276
00:11:52.254 --> 00:11:54.256
Sir. we found her.

277
00:11:54.339 --> 00:11:56.383
♪♪

278
00:12:02.097 --> 00:12:04.599
[alarm blaring]

279
00:12:10.981 --> 00:12:12.732
What is your agent doing in our building?

280
00:12:12.816 --> 00:12:14.443
Just... so lovely to see you. Amanda.

281
00:12:15.444 --> 00:12:17.154
[Sam] Please. Please. don't do this.

282
00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:18.864
Agents cannot be seen in here!

283
00:12:18.947 --> 00:12:21.825
There's protocol. you know that!
This is off-limits!

284
00:12:21.908 --> 00:12:23.952
♪♪

285
00:12:25.537 --> 00:12:26.788
[Sam] No.

286
00:12:33.795 --> 00:12:35.755
[telephone ringing]

287
00:12:51.980 --> 00:12:53.482
He says. "Let her up."

288
00:12:54.941 --> 00:12:56.818
-[pounding on door]
-[Debbie] Judith!

289
00:12:56.902 --> 00:12:59.112
Judith! Judith!

290
00:13:00.489 --> 00:13:01.823
[straining]

291
00:13:01.907 --> 00:13:03.909
[quiet. suspenseful music playing]

292
00:13:05.535 --> 00:13:07.120
[panting]

293
00:13:15.003 --> 00:13:16.671
[quietly] Okay.

294
00:13:16.755 --> 00:13:18.840
Okay. here we go.

295
00:13:18.924 --> 00:13:21.426
There are four numbers.

296
00:13:21.510 --> 00:13:23.720
Which means...

297
00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:27.599
like. 10.000 possible combinations. Oh...

298
00:13:29.893 --> 00:13:31.686
Unless...

299
00:13:31.770 --> 00:13:33.480
I know the four numbers.

300
00:13:33.563 --> 00:13:35.565
♪♪

301
00:13:35.649 --> 00:13:36.650
Oh...

302
00:13:44.199 --> 00:13:46.868
[beeping rapidly]

303
00:13:53.083 --> 00:13:54.292
Really. Judith?

304
00:13:57.045 --> 00:13:58.296
-[beeping stops]
-[exhales]

305
00:13:59.089 --> 00:14:00.966
[scoffs]

306
00:14:07.055 --> 00:14:09.057
[quiet. dramatic music playing]

307
00:14:16.147 --> 00:14:18.775
Yes. quite. smash them down. why not?

308
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:21.361
What's 200 years of Moroccan craftsmanship

309
00:14:21.444 --> 00:14:22.529
when you're in a hurry?

310
00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:24.155
What the fuck is this?

311
00:14:26.241 --> 00:14:28.034
The Black Mark.

312
00:14:28.118 --> 00:14:29.869
How thrilling. About time

313
00:14:29.953 --> 00:14:31.121
somebody brought that back.

314
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:33.206
And from the "Book of Judith."

315
00:14:33.290 --> 00:14:34.874
Someone has done their homework.

316
00:14:34.958 --> 00:14:36.668
[Judith] Someone knew I was coming.

317
00:14:36.751 --> 00:14:38.878
so your system has been compromised.

318
00:14:38.962 --> 00:14:40.380
Impossible.

319
00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:42.215
Well. then. who ordered the hit?

320
00:14:42.299 --> 00:14:43.484
The only people that knew I was there:

321
00:14:43.508 --> 00:14:46.011
Me. you. Sam and whoever paid for the job.

322
00:14:46.094 --> 00:14:48.555
I need not remind you
of our security protocols.

323
00:14:48.638 --> 00:14:50.890
We are untraceable. unbreakable.

324
00:14:50.974 --> 00:14:55.186
because even if I wanted
to give you that information. I cannot.

325
00:14:55.270 --> 00:14:57.647
So. in answer to your quandary.

326
00:14:57.731 --> 00:15:01.526
why don't you find
this Billy Donovan and ask him?

327
00:15:02.652 --> 00:15:05.363
Before you kill him. obviously.

328
00:15:05.447 --> 00:15:07.782
And you ask me what these are.

329
00:15:07.866 --> 00:15:11.202
And the answer is
they are merely pieces of paper

330
00:15:11.286 --> 00:15:13.580
to which we have attributed meaning.

331
00:15:15.707 --> 00:15:17.876
What they symbolize to you

332
00:15:17.959 --> 00:15:20.920
is that someone is coming.

333
00:15:22.005 --> 00:15:23.882
What they symbolize to me...

334
00:15:25.342 --> 00:15:29.054
is that you can no longer do your job.

335
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:32.182
The girl I trained

336
00:15:32.265 --> 00:15:34.976
would never have allowed this to happen.

337
00:15:35.060 --> 00:15:37.354
You grow weak.

338
00:15:37.437 --> 00:15:39.939
your work is sloppy.

339
00:15:40.023 --> 00:15:44.027
Austria. Brussels. Beirut.
rule breaking. ignoring the plan...

340
00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:45.362
-No. that was different.
-No!

341
00:15:46.529 --> 00:15:48.657
It is not.

342
00:15:49.741 --> 00:15:51.117
You disobeyed

343
00:15:51.201 --> 00:15:55.038
and allowed yourself
to be compromised. and now.

344
00:15:55.121 --> 00:15:56.498
someone has found you.

345
00:15:56.581 --> 00:16:00.043
You are not what you once were.

346
00:16:00.126 --> 00:16:01.378
You were my best.

347
00:16:01.461 --> 00:16:02.629
No. I still am.

348
00:16:02.712 --> 00:16:04.047
Prove it.

349
00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:07.884
You're no agent of mine until you complete
the job you were hired to do.

350
00:16:12.597 --> 00:16:14.432
Oh. and Whiptail?

351
00:16:16.685 --> 00:16:19.187
Don't ever fucking come in here again.

352
00:16:19.896 --> 00:16:21.898
♪♪

353
00:16:29.781 --> 00:16:31.866
[birds singing]

354
00:16:38.707 --> 00:16:40.709
[creaking]

355
00:16:46.673 --> 00:16:47.674
Hmm.

356
00:17:06.025 --> 00:17:07.318
[sighs]

357
00:17:24.002 --> 00:17:25.670
What have you done?

358
00:17:26.838 --> 00:17:29.090
[tense. dramatic music playing]

359
00:17:30.717 --> 00:17:32.010
[exhales]

360
00:17:52.655 --> 00:17:53.656
[object clatters]

361
00:18:11.841 --> 00:18:12.967
-[sighs]
-[turns phone on]

362
00:18:16.012 --> 00:18:17.680
♪♪

363
00:18:28.733 --> 00:18:30.318
[glass shatters]

364
00:18:32.946 --> 00:18:34.739
[latch rattles]

365
00:18:34.823 --> 00:18:35.824
[door opens]

366
00:18:35.907 --> 00:18:37.826
[glass crunching]

367
00:18:41.621 --> 00:18:43.623
[suspenseful music playing]

368
00:18:55.885 --> 00:18:57.136
[line ringing]

369
00:18:57.220 --> 00:18:58.805
[operator] 999. What's your emergency?

370
00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:00.533
Yes. there are people
breaking into my house.

371
00:19:00.557 --> 00:19:02.559
I'm at 17 Rosemoor Lane.

372
00:19:02.642 --> 00:19:04.644
-Speak up. please.
-No. I can't speak up because

373
00:19:04.727 --> 00:19:06.145
there are men breaking in.

374
00:19:06.229 --> 00:19:08.022
Okay. can you describe these men for me?

375
00:19:08.106 --> 00:19:10.942
No. no. no. no. because
they are downstairs and I'm upstairs.

376
00:19:11.025 --> 00:19:12.920
And I think it's the same people
who murdered my husband

377
00:19:12.944 --> 00:19:14.129
and now they are gonna murder me.

378
00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:15.530
Check the bedroom.

379
00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:16.799
-Fuck.
-They murdered your husband

380
00:19:16.823 --> 00:19:18.032
in your house?

381
00:19:18.116 --> 00:19:19.701
-Is that right?
-No. No. no. no. no. no.

382
00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:22.704
They murdered him last night
at the Water Relief gala.

383
00:19:22.787 --> 00:19:25.140
I don't have any reports of
a murder at a Water Relief gala.

384
00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:27.375
That's because a mold company took him.

385
00:19:27.458 --> 00:19:29.085
A mold company murdered your husband?

386
00:19:29.168 --> 00:19:31.588
No. No. they didn't murder him.
they just took him.

387
00:19:32.630 --> 00:19:34.465
They're a front
for an assassination agency.

388
00:19:34.549 --> 00:19:36.301
What part of this is difficult?

389
00:19:37.969 --> 00:19:40.263
Oh. God. Oh. God.

390
00:19:40.346 --> 00:19:42.640
♪♪

391
00:20:02.368 --> 00:20:04.287
[Debbie grunting]

392
00:20:04.370 --> 00:20:06.372
[dramatic music playing]

393
00:20:21.095 --> 00:20:23.222
[tense dramatic music playing]

394
00:20:41.491 --> 00:20:42.867
[cell phone buzzes. chimes]

395
00:20:44.994 --> 00:20:46.996
♪♪

396
00:21:08.893 --> 00:21:10.895
♪♪

397
00:21:20.655 --> 00:21:22.365
[cell phone buzzes. chimes]

398
00:21:31.833 --> 00:21:33.835
♪♪

399
00:21:36.504 --> 00:21:38.881
[cell phone buzzes. chimes]

400
00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:08.161
♪♪

401
00:22:26.721 --> 00:22:28.723
[car alarms blaring]

402
00:22:29.849 --> 00:22:31.893
[Judith whimpers]

403
00:22:37.690 --> 00:22:39.400
[coughing]

404
00:22:39.484 --> 00:22:41.360
♪♪

405
00:22:41.444 --> 00:22:43.946
[indistinct chatter]

406
00:22:50.828 --> 00:22:51.913
Ooh.

407
00:22:52.955 --> 00:22:55.083
-Who did that?
-Uh...

408
00:22:56.167 --> 00:22:57.919
guy in. uh. Lebanon.

409
00:22:58.002 --> 00:23:00.755
Hmm. [chuckles] Does good work.

410
00:23:00.838 --> 00:23:03.341
-[Judith winces]
-Yeah. Tight stitches.

411
00:23:03.424 --> 00:23:05.551
Not as good as me. but

412
00:23:05.635 --> 00:23:07.303
it's good.

413
00:23:09.388 --> 00:23:10.932
You gonna tell me what happened?

414
00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:14.644
Someone try to kill ya?

415
00:23:15.853 --> 00:23:17.814
Far worse. Someone's playing me.

416
00:23:20.066 --> 00:23:23.027
They could've killed me so many times.
and they're not...

417
00:23:23.111 --> 00:23:24.237
they're not doing it.

418
00:23:25.238 --> 00:23:26.572
Who?

419
00:23:27.782 --> 00:23:29.867
-I don't know. I-I...
-Sorry.

420
00:23:31.244 --> 00:23:32.995
They're so far ahead of me.

421
00:23:33.079 --> 00:23:35.706
they know every move I'm making. I'm...

422
00:23:35.790 --> 00:23:37.291
I was tailing the mark.

423
00:23:37.375 --> 00:23:39.877
but he was. he was leading me there.

424
00:23:40.962 --> 00:23:43.172
I walked straight into it.

425
00:23:44.215 --> 00:23:46.676
Not permanently. but

426
00:23:46.759 --> 00:23:47.969
just for a little while.

427
00:23:48.052 --> 00:23:50.596
-why don't you take a step back?
-[sighs]

428
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:53.683
Get your head in the right place.

429
00:23:53.766 --> 00:23:55.560
I can't step back.

430
00:23:55.643 --> 00:23:57.728
[quiet. dramatic music playing]

431
00:23:57.812 --> 00:23:59.605
He'll never let me back in.

432
00:23:59.689 --> 00:24:01.691
Is that the worst thing?

433
00:24:02.775 --> 00:24:04.443
I can't think of anything worse.

434
00:24:06.279 --> 00:24:07.905
This is all I have.

435
00:24:10.158 --> 00:24:11.450
It's all I am.

436
00:24:13.536 --> 00:24:16.289
[quiet music playing]

437
00:24:18.499 --> 00:24:20.659
[news anchor] We are now going
live to Milgate Cemetery

438
00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:23.337
with a report that some viewers
may find distressing.

439
00:24:23.421 --> 00:24:26.591
[reporter] Residents of this
quiet suburb in North London

440
00:24:26.674 --> 00:24:27.967
have been left reeling...

441
00:24:28.050 --> 00:24:29.444
-My God.
-following the discovery

442
00:24:29.468 --> 00:24:31.637
of local resident. Martin Shaw.

443
00:24:31.721 --> 00:24:34.515
a Milgate Cemetery groundskeeper
who was found

444
00:24:34.599 --> 00:24:35.683
murdered last night

445
00:24:35.766 --> 00:24:38.352
in what the police have revealed
to be a single gunshot wound...

446
00:24:38.436 --> 00:24:40.354
[suspenseful music playing]

447
00:24:50.615 --> 00:24:52.617
[indistinct chatter]

448
00:24:52.700 --> 00:24:54.744
[cell phone ringing]

449
00:24:54.827 --> 00:24:56.204
[groans]

450
00:24:58.289 --> 00:25:00.708
[Judith] Hi. I was just checking in
to see how you're doing.

451
00:25:00.791 --> 00:25:01.709
Where are you?

452
00:25:01.792 --> 00:25:03.794
I'm at home. where you left me.

453
00:25:03.878 --> 00:25:07.048
Look. here's your stupid water tap.

454
00:25:08.090 --> 00:25:10.927
Oh. Good. good. Listen.
I need you to do something for me.

455
00:25:11.010 --> 00:25:12.970
-What is it?
-Right. there's a cupboard

456
00:25:13.054 --> 00:25:15.056
next to the fridge
that has a secret panel.

457
00:25:15.139 --> 00:25:17.058
-Mm-hmm.
-Can you open that for me?

458
00:25:17.141 --> 00:25:19.393
-There's some papers inside.
-Yep. Got 'em.

459
00:25:19.477 --> 00:25:22.146
Could you read me the third line
of the second page?

460
00:25:23.606 --> 00:25:27.526
[sighs] I-It's blurry.
I don't have my glasses.

461
00:25:27.610 --> 00:25:28.962
For fuck's sake!
I know you're not in my apartment

462
00:25:28.986 --> 00:25:30.196
because I'm in my apartment!

463
00:25:30.279 --> 00:25:31.822
Okay. fine. I left.

464
00:25:31.906 --> 00:25:33.407
How did you even get out?

465
00:25:33.491 --> 00:25:36.244
Your door combination is the same
as the passcode to your phone.

466
00:25:36.327 --> 00:25:37.954
You know what?

467
00:25:38.037 --> 00:25:40.373
I don't even want to talk to you.

468
00:25:40.456 --> 00:25:42.458
You killed that poor man in the cemetery

469
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:44.126
-last night.
-No. I didn't.

470
00:25:44.210 --> 00:25:45.336
Well. he's dead.

471
00:25:45.419 --> 00:25:46.879
and he's on the news.

472
00:25:46.963 --> 00:25:49.131
so I can only assume that you are lying

473
00:25:49.215 --> 00:25:52.236
since you've lied about everything for
every second that I've ever known you.

474
00:25:52.260 --> 00:25:55.721
No. no. I-I-I'm not lying.
I just didn't tell you.

475
00:25:55.805 --> 00:25:57.324
-Well. it's the same thing.
-No. Debbie.

476
00:25:57.348 --> 00:26:00.935
you're not hearing me.
I am trying to keep you safe.

477
00:26:01.018 --> 00:26:03.562
It is not your job to keep me safe.

478
00:26:03.646 --> 00:26:04.563
You. David.

479
00:26:04.647 --> 00:26:07.566
nobody gets to tell me
what's best for me. Not anymore.

480
00:26:07.650 --> 00:26:09.068
I'll handle this on my own.

481
00:26:09.151 --> 00:26:10.403
[call beeps off]

482
00:26:10.486 --> 00:26:11.486
[cell phone buzzes]

483
00:26:12.697 --> 00:26:14.365
[Sam] Whiptail. just so you know.

484
00:26:14.448 --> 00:26:15.908
I know Billy Donovan is not dead

485
00:26:15.992 --> 00:26:18.220
because I'm currently watching
a live feed of him looking...

486
00:26:18.244 --> 00:26:19.954
-Oh. damn.
-extremely alive and well.

487
00:26:20.037 --> 00:26:22.015
I've got the location
of his meeting this afternoon.

488
00:26:22.039 --> 00:26:23.916
and I'm texting it to you now.

489
00:26:25.293 --> 00:26:27.295
-[suspenseful. dramatic music playing]
-[sighs]

490
00:26:34.927 --> 00:26:36.929
[busy chatter]

491
00:26:38.347 --> 00:26:39.682
[Billy] Hey.

492
00:26:39.765 --> 00:26:41.475
Gentlemen.

493
00:26:41.559 --> 00:26:42.977
How are we?

494
00:26:45.479 --> 00:26:46.856
Right.

495
00:26:46.939 --> 00:26:49.233
Where's your friend?

496
00:26:49.317 --> 00:26:51.110
I'm. uh. famished. fellas.

497
00:26:51.193 --> 00:26:53.237
What're we having? Anyone want to. uh.

498
00:26:53.321 --> 00:26:54.655
go halves on a seafood platter?

499
00:26:54.739 --> 00:26:56.782
Where is he?

500
00:26:56.866 --> 00:26:58.492
-Hmm?
-Your friend.

501
00:26:58.576 --> 00:27:00.161
David Claybourne.

502
00:27:00.244 --> 00:27:02.538
He's just. he-he's a little bit delayed.

503
00:27:02.621 --> 00:27:04.999
On account of. uh. being...

504
00:27:06.125 --> 00:27:07.126
dead.

505
00:27:07.209 --> 00:27:08.854
-What the... What'd you say?
-[Albon speaking Albanian]

506
00:27:08.878 --> 00:27:10.963
Hey. relax.

507
00:27:11.047 --> 00:27:12.631
♪♪

508
00:27:12.715 --> 00:27:15.926
Look. I know this isn't what
we would call...

509
00:27:16.010 --> 00:27:17.053
ideal.

510
00:27:18.137 --> 00:27:19.472
But I've got a plan.

511
00:27:21.057 --> 00:27:22.475
There's his wife.

512
00:27:22.558 --> 00:27:24.769
She knows everything about the operation.

513
00:27:24.852 --> 00:27:25.978
she's the brains of it.

514
00:27:26.062 --> 00:27:27.229
She's gone missing.

515
00:27:27.313 --> 00:27:29.648
We find her...

516
00:27:29.732 --> 00:27:31.859
we find the money.

517
00:27:31.942 --> 00:27:34.737
And how do you intend to find her?

518
00:27:34.820 --> 00:27:37.448
[Debbie] Good afternoon. gentlemen.

519
00:27:37.531 --> 00:27:40.868
I do. uh. apologize
for interrupting your meeting.

520
00:27:40.951 --> 00:27:42.453
Now...

521
00:27:44.663 --> 00:27:46.916
Mister... Donovan?

522
00:27:46.999 --> 00:27:48.042
I would like to know

523
00:27:48.125 --> 00:27:51.504
the exact nature of your business
with my husband.

524
00:27:52.963 --> 00:27:54.590
[scoffs]

525
00:27:54.673 --> 00:27:56.300
Who the fuck are you?

526
00:27:56.384 --> 00:27:58.761
How rude of me.

527
00:27:58.844 --> 00:28:01.514
I'm sorry. My name is Debbie Claybourne.

528
00:28:01.597 --> 00:28:04.934
I won't be long.
I just have some questions for Billy.

529
00:28:06.727 --> 00:28:08.187
This is the wife?

530
00:28:08.270 --> 00:28:11.440
Yes. this is the wife. And who are you?

531
